title: Random Beau Thought
body:
Like many humans (and ogres), we have layers and one of the things I love about Critical Role and what the cast does is they create these fleshed out, 3D characters with multiple layers. And seeing this process from the beginning with the M9 campaign is really fun for me because I get to think (way too hard) about why.

As time goes on and the M9 spend more time together we’re starting to see some of these second layers. One example being Caleb’s high charisma coming through while Fjord was gone and that charming Empire boi peeking out. Another, and the most recent, being that little piece of darkness with Fjord and Algar. The relatively neutral and charming Texan dipped his toe into the bad bitch pool. Who knows why? There’s a lot of questions surrounding why Jester is so cheery and bubbly, even while bound and gagged after being kidnapped. And what even is Yasha, I just know there’s so much behind those sexy barbarian eyes…

But one that I simply can’t wrap my head around is Beau. Other than the rather occasional moments that warranted emotion (ie: Molly; finding the stolen 3), the only layer we have seen from Beau is the angry, rude, asshole (respectfully). Not to mention, we’ve only heard a small piece of her backstory, so of course there’s so much more to come that I know will eventually be laid out but for now I’m just genuinely curious. 

Beau has mentioned a few times that she’s never really had friends, only people she’s worked with, you know for crimes and shit. So why stick around with the M9? What’s the difference between them and the people before? Another thing that has always bothered me (but probably shouldn’t really), up until Clay everyone of the Nine had a partner, albeit in some cases not that long but still. 

Jester and Fjord, 

Nott and Caleb, 

Molly and Yasha. 

They all had time together before meeting up, except Beau. Beau only knew Jester and Fjord roughly a day or two before meeting the rest of the group. Again, I don’t really know what any of this could mean, if anything at all, it just has me wondering.

In the end, there really is no result from this intrigue. One pitiful theory I had about Beau is that I think that hardened and angry persona is to cover a genuine fear Beau has, specifically of her family. I think Beau is terrified of her father and going home to see him. Do I have viable proof to back this up… NO of course not! So until it all actually reaches the surface and we learn who the true Beauregard is, I will question everything.
